 and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705192,"age":54,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705193,"age":63,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705195,"age":108,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Lora Picott was born after 1273, in Warwickshire, England, her father, Michael Picot, was 8757 and her mother, Joan Wake, was 8745. She married Gerald Braybrooke Sr about 1289, in Warwickshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Aft 1273–":"pärast 1273–Surnud","1273–Female":"1273–Surnud","1284–Male":"1284–Surnud","1286–Male":"1286–Surnud","1264–1324":"1264–1324","1307–1359":"1307–1359","1242–1278":"1242–1278","1255–1300":"1255–1300","1242":"1242","1264":"1264","1286":"1286","1284":"1284","1273":"1273","1382":"1382","1290":"1290","Abt 1285":"umbes 1285","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1359":"1359","